WEBVTT

00:18.017 --> 00:19.936
<i>Previously on </i>You:

00:20.020 --> 00:23.064
<i>You are a monster and a killer.</i>

00:23.940 --> 00:26.568
<i>One of you fuckers sent me those texts.</i>

00:26.651 --> 00:28.236
<i>"Hello, Joe."</i>

00:29.279 --> 00:32.490
<i>"You like it. How it feels. To kill."</i>

00:32.574 --> 00:34.743
Somebody's trying to frame me.

00:38.830 --> 00:41.624
You don't want to fuck.
You want to make love.

00:41.708 --> 00:43.418
You don't know who I am or what I want.

00:43.501 --> 00:47.714
You're trying to seem noble
while you hide your true motives.

00:47.797 --> 00:49.340
<i>"It's time for us to meet."</i>

00:49.883 --> 00:51.760
<i>When and where?</i>

00:53.303 --> 00:55.305
<i>This can't be good.</i>

01:04.647 --> 01:08.401
<i>Here I was, thinking you've ended</i>
<i>my second lease on life</i>

01:08.485 --> 01:10.278
<i>before it's even begun, but really,</i>

01:10.361 --> 01:12.906
<i>we were about</i>
<i>to be pulled closer than ever.</i>

01:12.989 --> 01:14.783
<i>-But first...</i>
-Professor Moore.

01:15.408 --> 01:17.744
If we might have
the briefest moment of your time.

01:18.286 --> 01:22.082
<i>I had to jump through</i>
<i>yet another insanely polite, British hoop.</i>

01:22.999 --> 01:24.751
Of course. Anything to help.

01:37.180 --> 01:40.099
It's nice to talk to somebody
comparatively sober.

01:40.183 --> 01:41.768
<i>They've grilled everyone.</i>

01:41.851 --> 01:44.687
We looked into the tip
you gave us, the artist Blue.

01:44.771 --> 01:47.190
Her story matched what you told us.

01:47.273 --> 01:49.108
Glad to hear that. Well, I'm...

01:49.818 --> 01:51.361
Of course I'm not glad.

01:51.444 --> 01:54.114
We're now pursuing
Simon's past associates.

01:54.197 --> 01:55.698
<i>Hope he had thousands.</i>

01:55.782 --> 01:59.119
Perhaps you've thought
of something else relevant.

01:59.202 --> 02:02.080
<i>So I'm off the hook</i>
<i>but not quite off the hook.</i>

02:02.163 --> 02:05.458
-Can I call you if I think of anything?
-Any time.

02:05.542 --> 02:08.545
Who knows, Jonathan,
you might have helped crack it.

02:08.628 --> 02:10.255
One can only hope.

02:11.297 --> 02:14.092
Well, until we speak again.

02:33.820 --> 02:37.031
<i>Hyenas. Disappointed nothing happened.</i>

02:37.115 --> 02:38.575
<i>Not because they care</i>
<i>their friends are dead</i>

02:38.658 --> 02:40.660
<i>but because they feel nothing.</i>

02:40.743 --> 02:42.871
<i>Their lives are so bubble-wrapped.</i>

02:43.454 --> 02:45.290
<i>They're already bored again.</i>

02:45.373 --> 02:47.625
<i>Meanwhile, you are keeping me riveted.</i>

02:47.709 --> 02:49.836
<i>Who are you, asshole?</i>

02:49.919 --> 02:51.296
<i>And how do I stop you?</i>

02:51.379 --> 02:53.464
Jonathan. Come, come.

02:55.884 --> 02:57.051
<i>Hampsie.</i>

02:57.135 --> 02:59.178
<i>Lady Phoebe's country house.</i>

02:59.262 --> 03:01.014
<i>Running away from the masses.</i>

03:01.097 --> 03:03.182
You're coming and cannot say, "No."

03:03.266 --> 03:05.476
<i>All of us under one roof.</i>

03:05.560 --> 03:08.521
It sounds a bit like a friend-group thing.

03:08.605 --> 03:10.398
We simply must have you there.

03:11.524 --> 03:13.860
<i>They don't know</i>
<i>they're bringing the killer with them.</i>

03:13.943 --> 03:16.112
<i>One of them is you.</i>

03:16.779 --> 03:18.114
Then I would love to.

03:42.639 --> 03:45.683
<i>Phoebe insisted "no gifts"</i>
<i>in the least convincing delivery</i>

03:45.767 --> 03:46.809
<i>I've ever heard.</i>

03:49.979 --> 03:52.774
<i>My rich neighbors drink</i>
<i>the kind of wine I could never afford.</i>

04:08.373 --> 04:10.375
<i>One thing is clear:</i>

04:10.458 --> 04:13.169
<i>If I'm going to seize the opportunity</i>
<i>this weekend provides,</i>

04:13.253 --> 04:15.797
<i>I need zero distractions.</i>

04:25.890 --> 04:28.101
Look, do you have the message or not?

04:28.184 --> 04:30.812
Don't leave out the part
where I tell him to keep his nose

04:30.895 --> 04:32.146
out of my business.

04:33.356 --> 04:35.233
No, I don't want to tell him.

04:35.316 --> 04:36.526
How many more years

04:36.609 --> 04:40.280
before you people understand
I do not want to speak to the man.

04:41.531 --> 04:42.782
Christ.

04:50.498 --> 04:53.042
You bled capital
on that tech venture.

04:53.126 --> 04:55.586
There's not a bank in London
you don't owe money to.

04:55.670 --> 04:58.506
There's the unpaid mortgages
in Shoreditch.

04:58.589 --> 05:01.259
Mortgages that were offered
against this club.

05:02.677 --> 05:05.513
Which I know you would hate to lose.

05:09.642 --> 05:12.770
You cannot go another day
without paying your lenders.

05:13.354 --> 05:16.482
They will come for more
than your assets. Destroy you.

05:16.566 --> 05:18.651
Ruin everything
you've worked hard to achieve.

05:18.735 --> 05:21.321
Robert, I get it.
I will call my dad if it's that bad.

05:21.404 --> 05:23.990
I recall him saying that last time was...

05:24.073 --> 05:25.742
Well, the last time.

05:25.825 --> 05:28.786
Well, yes,
but he didn't actually mean that.

05:28.870 --> 05:32.290
-Oh, shoot. I actually have to jet. Sorry.
-No, no.

05:32.373 --> 05:34.625
-Please consider staying.
-I'll call my dad from the car.

05:34.709 --> 05:38.254
Everybody is gonna
get their money on time.

05:39.672 --> 05:40.882
Enjoy the country.

05:42.508 --> 05:43.342
Thank you.

06:19.796 --> 06:22.673
<i>It's nice to think, when I return,</i>

06:22.757 --> 06:24.967
<i>I'll have put you behind me.</i>

06:25.051 --> 06:27.762
<i>Maybe life can finally return to normal.</i>

06:50.409 --> 06:54.288
<i>So this is what the Blaxworths mean</i>
<i>by "little country house."</i>

07:03.714 --> 07:04.549
Hi.

07:08.719 --> 07:11.889
<i>Seems more to me</i>
<i>like </i>Downton Abbey<i> vampire castle.</i>

07:26.863 --> 07:29.282
-Welcome to Hampsbridge, sir.
-Thank you.

07:29.365 --> 07:30.783
-Thanks.
-You.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.412
You rather stick out, don't you?

07:35.913 --> 07:39.584
So is she shagging you? Phoebe?
Or are you more decorative?

07:39.667 --> 07:40.668
<i>She is so sweet.</i>

07:40.751 --> 07:43.045
Is it true, though,
American men are better in bed?

07:43.129 --> 07:44.964
Or is it only the Jewish ones?

07:45.047 --> 07:46.257
<i>Is it legal to say that?</i>

07:46.340 --> 07:48.092
Joking! We're having a laugh.

07:48.176 --> 07:50.344
Please try and have a sense of humor.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.513
<i>I will, if she starts being funny.</i>

07:52.597 --> 07:54.807
Oh, no. My ex is here.

07:56.726 --> 07:58.686
<i>Awful enough to be you</i>
<i>if she had the smarts.</i>

07:58.769 --> 08:00.313
<i>No evidence she does.</i>

08:00.396 --> 08:03.232
The bastard gave me gonor-rona
in the Seychelles.

08:03.316 --> 08:04.942
No one had a worse 2020 than me.

08:05.485 --> 08:08.029
-Why can't the killer chop up all my exes?
-<i>Huh.</i>

08:08.112 --> 08:10.448
<i>Or Gemma, if you're taking requests.</i>

08:10.531 --> 08:11.616
<i>No. No.</i>

08:11.699 --> 08:14.327
<i>Delightful as that would be,</i>
<i>I'm here to stop you, so...</i>

08:15.995 --> 08:18.164
<i>Which one are you?</i>

08:25.213 --> 08:26.631
Well, lovely chat,

08:26.714 --> 08:29.717
but I'm off to hang myself
because you're so boring.

08:30.343 --> 08:32.887
I'm joking. But do better.

08:35.848 --> 08:38.601
Look, no one is even
noticing them, darling.

08:38.684 --> 08:41.395
I notice them. And I don't want them here.

08:42.355 --> 08:43.981
Sorry. It's not your fault.

08:44.482 --> 08:47.151
Just ignore them.
At least we know we're safe.

08:48.319 --> 08:49.779
Yes, I suppose we do.

08:58.955 --> 09:00.831
<i>Like I said,</i>
<i>I can't afford distractions.</i>

09:00.915 --> 09:02.708
<i>-Not now.</i>
-Jonathan.

09:02.792 --> 09:04.043
You're here!

09:04.126 --> 09:05.878
It'll mostly be hunting.

09:06.712 --> 09:09.173
-Do you hunt?
-I have, once or twice.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.759
It's exhilarating, if you're a good shot.

09:11.842 --> 09:14.887
Didn't your own vice president
shoot someone in the face?

09:14.971 --> 09:18.474
Yeah, some may have wished
it went the other way.

09:19.100 --> 09:20.101
A wit.

09:21.852 --> 09:24.730
I've always admired a man like you who...

09:25.356 --> 09:27.191
doesn't care how he presents.

09:28.651 --> 09:30.278
I'm so pleased you're here.

09:32.905 --> 09:36.492
<i>You really could be any of these monsters.</i>

09:40.079 --> 09:41.163
Come, come.

09:41.247 --> 09:43.374
Let the festivities commence.

09:43.457 --> 09:44.458
Ooh!

09:49.005 --> 09:50.631
<i>Bring on the hunt.</i>

09:58.973 --> 10:02.018
Lord Tennyson found this
to be the best view of the grounds.

10:02.101 --> 10:03.894
He spent hours a day taking it in.

10:06.772 --> 10:09.734
You'll have trouble with that.
No service or Wi-Fi.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.569
<i>You're kidding me.</i>

10:11.652 --> 10:13.946
I'm sure if Lord Tennyson managed...

10:14.030 --> 10:15.948
Most of our guests come to appreciate it.

10:16.032 --> 10:17.658
<i>Most guests</i>
<i>don't have to communicate</i>

10:17.742 --> 10:19.160
<i>with a killer intent on texting.</i>

10:22.872 --> 10:24.999
<i>A picture emerges.</i>

10:25.082 --> 10:28.044
<i>No Internet, no security cams,</i>
<i>even the light switches are 50 years old.</i>

10:28.127 --> 10:30.796
<i>This isn't another house.</i>
<i>It's another world.</i>

10:30.880 --> 10:32.840
<i>Must feel incredibly safe to them</i>

10:32.923 --> 10:34.717
<i>and remarkably private to you.</i>

10:37.845 --> 10:39.722
-Oh.
-<i>Adjoining doors.</i>

10:39.805 --> 10:41.015
<i>Of course.</i>

10:41.098 --> 10:44.644
Someone must have fallen in favor
with the lady of the manor.

10:45.227 --> 10:47.855
